# Goals — production auth, secrets, payments

What "production ready" means for the account layer, graded like
[[docs/GOALS.local-agent]]: each goal has a definition of done you can test.

Current substrate (already live):
- Worker (reactable.app, CF + KV + R2): Google OAuth (`/api/auth/login|callback`),
  HMAC-sealed sessions, `/api/auth/me`, **CLI device flow** (`/api/auth/cli/start|poll`),
  YouTube OAuth connect/callback, DMG + model downloads.
- CLI: `reactable auth login|status|logout` → `~/.reactable/credentials.json`.
- App: Settings sign-in is a bare link; panel reads `~/.reactable/auth.json`
  (plan gates the Pro strip). **File mismatch: CLI writes credentials.json,
  panel reads auth.json.**
- Secrets: BYO connector keys + MiniMax key local, plaintext, injected
  server-side by the local nexus (never enter the model transcript).
- Payments: nothing. Design doc: [[docs/explorations/MINIMAX-GATEWAY]].
  `auth.ts` header names Polar as the intended processor.

## G1 — One identity spine
Settings "Sign in" runs the EXISTING device flow (worker `cli/start` +
`cli/poll`, driven by the native panel), lands one canonical credential file
(`~/.reactable/auth.json`; `credentials.json` becomes a symlink or dies), and
pushes account state into the panel live. CLI and app read the same file;
`/api/auth/me` is the single truth for `{email, plan, credits}`.
**DoD:** sign in from Settings → coin/plan state updates without relaunch;
`reactable auth status` and the panel agree; logout clears both.

## G2 — Session security
Sessions get expiry + sliding refresh; device-flow codes are single-use,
TTL'd, rate-limited; OAuth `state` verified; cookies HttpOnly/Secure/SameSite;
`AUTH_SECRET` + OAuth client secrets live only in `wrangler secret` (audit the
repo/history); revocation = KV delete honored everywhere.
**DoD:** replayed device code fails; stolen expired cookie fails; secret scan
of repo+history clean.

## G3 — Secret boundaries (the rule of two vaults)
Local vault: BYO keys (Pexels/Unsplash/ElevenLabs/FAL, MiniMax) stay
local-only — move to 0600 (or Keychain later), never sync, never transcript.
Cloud vault: Pro-integration OAuth tokens (YouTube/Meta/Drive) live ONLY in
worker KV, AES-GCM envelope-encrypted per user; the app gets short-lived
scoped calls through the gateway, never the refresh token. The Scrape
Creators key exists ONLY as a worker secret — it has no local existence and
no customer-visible name.
**DoD:** grep of `~/.reactable` shows zero third-party OAuth refresh tokens;
worker responses never echo tokens; connectors.json chmod 0600.

## G4 — Payments + plan state (Polar)
Polar (merchant of record — handles VAT/tax for a solo op) with two products:
**Pro $20/mo** subscription; **credit packs** for the model gateway. Webhooks
(signature-verified, idempotent) write plan/credits to KV keyed by user;
`/api/auth/me` carries them; the app refreshes auth.json on launch + daily.
Customer portal link in Settings for manage/cancel.
**DoD:** test-mode subscribe → PRO coin in app ≤1 min; cancel → downgrade on
next refresh; webhook replay does not double-credit.

## G5 — Credits gateway (MiniMax metering)
Per [[docs/explorations/MINIMAX-GATEWAY]]: worker endpoint proxying chat
completions with SSE passthrough, per-user ledger (D1 or a Durable Object for
atomicity), surcharge on top of MiniMax cost, fail-closed at zero balance.
Signed-in users without a BYO key route through it; BYO keys bypass free.
**DoD:** two concurrent streams can't overspend the ledger; charge ≈ usage
reconciles per stream; balance-exhausted mid-stream ends cleanly with a
clear in-panel message.

## G6 — Pro integrations (YouTube · Meta · Drive)
Worker OAuth per provider (YouTube exists — regate it), tokens per G3, all
gated on plan=pro. The nexus `connector` tool grows gateway-backed providers:
auth = user session token, worker swaps in the integration token server-side.
First verbs: YouTube upload (unlisted), Drive file import → assets/, Meta
campaign read. Scrape-creators-backed research is surfaced only as "brand
intelligence / consumer research".
**DoD:** connect YouTube from Settings → agent posts an unlisted test video;
non-pro account gets a clean upsell error naming the plan, not the vendor.

## G7 — Client trust
Notarize the DMG (signing already done); update check against
`/api/download` with version + hash; worker API versioning (`/api/v1/…`) so
old clients degrade politely.
**DoD:** fresh Mac: download → open with no Gatekeeper override; old client
against new worker gets JSON "upgrade" not a 500.

## G8 — Ops + compliance floor
Rate limits per IP+user on auth/gateway routes; structured worker logs with
error alerting; KV/D1 export cron; privacy policy + ToS pages; account-delete
endpoint that purges sessions, tokens, ledger.
**DoD:** delete-account leaves zero KV keys for the user; a synthetic 5xx
spike alerts.

## Order
G1 → G4 → G3 → G6 → G5, with G2 continuous and G7/G8 before public launch.
Rationale: identity unification unblocks everything; payments make the plan
real; boundaries before integrations carry real tokens; the credits gateway
is the deepest build and shouldn't block Pro launch.

